SEC. 2.

Purposes and objectives.

âThe PVTA shall have Ike following purposes and objectives:

To promote the effective merchandizing of Virginia tobacco in the domestic and foreign markets so that those engaged in the industry will be placed on a basis of economic security;

To establish and maintain balanced production and consumption of Virginia Tobacco and its manufactured products, and such marketing conditions as will insure and stabilize the price at a level sufficient to cover the cost of production plus reasonable profit both in the local as well as in the foreign market;

To create, establish, maintain, and operate processing, warehousing and marketing facilities in suitable centers and supervise the selling and buying of Virginia tobacco so that the farmers will enjoy reasonable prices that secure a fair return of their investments;

To prescribe rules and regulations governing the grading, classifying, and inspecting of Virginia tobacco; and

To improve the living and economic conditions of the people engaged in the tobacco industry.

SEC. 4.

Specific Powers.

âThe PVTA is authorized and directed:

To take over and assume, and thereafter exclusively direct, supervise, and control, all functions and operations with respect to the processing, warehousing, and trading of Virginia tobacco, the provisions of any existing Jaw to the contrary notwithstanding;

To buy Virginia tobacco grown in the Philippines for resale to local

bona fide

tobacco manufacturers and leaf tobacco dealers;

To give priority in the purchase of the Virginia tobacco that are sold through farmers' cooperative marketing associations, or federations thereof, dealing principally, in Virginia tobacco, or any 100% Filipino firm or corporation the majority of the stocks of which are owned by said farmers' cooperative marketing associations, or federations thereof, and to utilize the facilities, of said associations, federations, firms, or corporations, in the buying of the farmers' produce;

To export directly or through farmers' cooperative marketing associations, or federations thereof, dealing principally in Virginia tobacco, or any 100% Filipino firm or corporation the majority of the stocks of which are owned by said farmers' cooperative marketing associations, or federations thereof, locally grown Virginia tobacco either through direct sales or barter:

Provided,

That in no case shall there be barter of locally grown leaf Virginia tobacco for foreign grown leaf Virginia tobacco or its manufactured products:

And provided, further,

That only such locally grown leaf Virginia tobacco as cannot be sold profitably in dollars may be bartered;

To give priority in the use of facilities, equipment, trucking service, warehouses, processing plants and machineries owned or operated by farmers' cooperative marketing associations, or federations thereof, dealing principally in Virginia tobacco, or any100% Filipino firm or corporation the-majority of the stocks of which are owned by said farmers' cooperative marketing associations, or federations thereof, to carry out the purpose of this Act;

To develop and expand the domestic and foreign markets for Virginia tobacco, its products and by-products in order to promote and expand production of Virginia tobacco, its products and by-products;

To grant loans and credits oil reasonable terms, for trading purposes, to farmers' cooperative marketing associations or federations thereof, dealing principally in Virginia tobacco, or any 100% Filipino firm or corporation the majority of the stocks of which are owned by said farmers' cooperative marketing associations or federations thereof, whenever it deems such loans necessary to carry out the provisions of this Act:

Provided,

That the interest charged shall not exceed seven per centum per annum;

To enter into, make and execute contracts of any kind as may be necessary or incidental to the attainment of its purposes with any person, firm, or corporation, with the Government of the Philippines or with any foreign government, subject to existing laws;

To promote, foster and encourage the organization of cooperative associations among tobacco planters, producers or dealers in Virginia tobacco producing regions in collaboration with the ACCFA;

SEC. 7.

Powers and duties of the Board of Directors.

â The Board of Directors shall have the following powers:

To prescribe, amend, modify or repeal by-laws, rules and regulations, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, governing the manner in which the general business of the PVTA may be done;

To appoint the General Manager and the Assistant General Manager, who shall receive a salary of twelve thousand pesos and nine thousand six hundred pesos per annum, respectively;

To confirm the appointments of other officials and employees of the PVTA, except the Auditor and the employees under him who shall be appointed by the Auditor General;

To approve the annual budget of the PVTA and/or such supplemental budgets thereof as may be proposed and submitted to the Board by the General Manager from time to time; and

To perform such other duties related to the, welfare of the tobacco industry as may be assigned to it by the President of the Philippines.

SEC. 8.

Powers and duties of the General Manager.

â The duties of the General Manager shall be:

To manage the affairs of the PVTA subject to the control and supervision of the Board of Directors;

To submit within sixty days before the beginning of each fiscal year and annual budget to the Board of Directors;

To appoint such subordinate officials and employees as may be necessary for the proper discharge of the duties and functions of the PVTA subject to the confirmation of the Board of Directors;

To perform such other duties as may be assigned to him by the Board of Directors from time to time;

To submit within sixty days after the close of the fiscal year an annual report to the President through the Board of Directors; and

To attend all the meetings of the Board and participate in deliberations thereof but not to vote.
